<PolicyLayout
  title="Cookie policy"
  description="How seoskill.dev uses cookie-free Clicky analytics without receiving local reports, tokens, or connected account data."
  dateModified="2026-07-23"
>
  <h1>Cookie policy</h1>
  <p>Last updated: 23 July 2026</p>
  <p>
    The seoskill.dev website uses Clicky to count visits and see which pages
    people use. Clicky tracking cookies are disabled in the website code.
  </p>
  <p>
    Clicky receives normal browser and request information such as the page,
    referrer, device, and IP address under its
    <a href="https://clicky.com/terms/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">privacy policy</a>.
    It does not receive your local reports, tokens, connected account data, or
    provider responses.
  </p>
  <p>
    The site is served through Cloudflare. Cloudflare may also process normal
    web request data and use strictly necessary security mechanisms under its
    own policies. The <a href="/privacy">privacy policy</a> explains how the
    website and local SEO software handle data separately.
  </p>
  <h2>Questions</h2>
  <p>
    Open an issue in the
    <a href="https://github.com/iannuttall/seo/issues">public GitHub repository</a>.
    Do not include tokens, private reports, personal data, or other secrets.
  </p>
</PolicyLayout>
